Comment:
SPOILERS FOR THE SUICIDE SQUAD

Is it just me, or are the Deadpool movies, Birds of Prey, and The Suicide Squad all extremely similar?

-Switches from PG-13 to R and doesn’t hold back with what they show (all 3)
-MC (main character) is from a group of superheroes (all 3)
-MC narrates throughout the entire movie (Deadpool and BOP)
-MC is occasionally hinted at the be a part of the LGBTQ+ community (Deadpool and BOP)
-MC has to protect a kid (Deadpool and BOP)
-By the end of the film, MC creates a new group with the kid they protected (Deadpool and BOP)
-Film mainly doesn’t happen in chronological order (Deadpool and POB, and a bit of TSQ)
-People are being experimented on (Deadpool and TSQ)
-Climax involves a building collapsing with the MC(s) inside it (Deadpool and TSQ)
-Considered to be much better than the previous movies they were based on (all 3)
-MC is dealing with the loss of a loved one throughout the film (all 3)
-MC(s) goes to prison at some point throughout the film (all 3, even though Harley Quinn isn’t arrested in BOP she does go into a prison)

R rated superhero movies need to be more original :P

Comment:
Sure, it's better than the first movie, but that's not saying much. Here's the thing: I love James Gunn, and what he did with GotG. The characters were cool cuz they were misfits, weirdos, and losers. What he did with The Suicide Squad was the complete opposite. He gave these "heroes" too much self-awareness. And once a character knows he's cool, he's no longer cool. You still with me? Enough with the slow-motion group walk towards the camera. Enough with the "quirky" soundtrack. Enough with the try-hard one-liners. Sure, make the action over-the-top, this is a comic book movie after all, but at least make it exciting !!

Margot Robbie rocks, tho. As usual.
